  "text": "## OpenTelemetry Span Creation Patterns Across Monitoring Stack\n\nThis analysis identifies how OpenTelemetry spans are created, annotated, and managed in prometheus/prometheus and grafana/grafana projects.\n\n### Tracer Initialization\n\n**Prometheus:**\n- `tracing/tracing.go` contains the core tracing infrastructure with the `Manager` type that handles tracer provider setup and lifecycle\n- `buildTracerProvider()` creates the tracer provider using OTLP exporters (gRPC or HTTP)\n- Uses `tracesdk.NewTracerProvider()` with batch exporting and sampling configuration\n- Registers the global text map propagator with `otel.SetTextMapPropagator()`\n\n**Grafana:**\n- Multiple services initialize tracers via `tracer.Start()` or `otel.GetTracerProvider().Tracer()`\n- Example in `apps/iam/pkg/reconcilers/zanzana_service.go`: `otel.GetTracerProvider().Tracer(\"iam-folder-reconciler\")`\n- Helper function in `pkg/promlib/utils/utils.go` provides `StartSpan()` wrapper for common patterns\n\n### Span Creation and Lifecycle\n\n**Common Pattern:**\n```go\nctx, span := tracer.Start(ctx, \"operation.name\")\ndefer span.End()\n```\n\n**Prometheus Examples:**\n- `storage/remote/queue_manager.go`: `createBatchSpan()` function creates spans for remote write batch operations\n- `scrape/scrape.go` (line 748): `otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, \"Scrape\", trace.WithSpanKind(trace.SpanKindClient))`\n- `rules/group.go` (line 515): Rule evaluation spans with context checking\n- `promql/engine.go` (line 1919): Expression evaluation spans\n\n**Grafana Examples:**\n- `pkg/bus/bus.go` (line 55): `b.tracer.Start(ctx, \"bus - \"+msgName)`\n- `pkg/expr/graph.go` (line 127): `s.tracer.Start(c, \"SSE.ExecuteNode\")`\n- `pkg/api/dashboard.go`: HTTP API handler spans with operation names like `\"api.GetDashboard\"`\n- `pkg/tsdb/loki/loki.go` (line 245): Datasource query spans\n\n### Span Attribute Setting\n\n**Prometheus:**\n- `storage/remote/queue_manager.go` (lines 2299-2305): Multiple attributes in single call:\n  ```go\n  span.SetAttributes(\n      attribute.Int(\"request_size\", sc.reqSize),\n      attribute.Int(\"samples\", sc.sampleCount),\n      attribute.String(\"remote_name\", remoteName),\n  )\n  ```\n- `rules/group.go` (line 516): `sp.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"name\", rule.Name()))`\n- `promql/engine.go` (line 1922): `span.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"operation\", ss.ShortString()))`\n\n**Grafana:**\n- `pkg/expr/graph.go` (lines 128-131): Multiple attribute types including StringSlice\n  ```go\n  span.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"node.refId\", node.RefID()))\n  span.SetAttributes(attribute.StringSlice(\"node.inputRefIDs\", inputRefIDs))\n  ```\n- `pkg/storage/unified/sql/db/otel/otel.go` (line 165): Custom DB instrumentation with driver and version attributes\n- `pkg/services/user/userimpl/user.go` (lines 268-270): Attributes set during span creation via `trace.WithAttributes()`\n- `pkg/infra/httpclient/httpclientprovider/tracing_middleware.go` (lines 40-41): Semantic convention attributes\n  ```go\n  span.SetAttributes(semconv.HTTPURL(req.URL.String()))\n  span.SetAttributes(semconv.HTTPMethod(req.Method))\n  ```\n\n### Span Error Recording\n\n**Grafana Patterns:**\n- `pkg/tsdb/tempo/trace.go` (lines 94-96):\n  ```go\n  span.RecordError(err)\n  span.SetStatus(codes.Error, err.Error())\n  ```\n- `pkg/registry/apis/provisioning/jobs/persistentstore.go` (line 242): `span.RecordError(err)`\n- `pkg/services/cloudmigration/api/api.go` (lines 93-94):\n  ```go\n  span.SetStatus(codes.Error, \"message\")\n  span.RecordError(err)\n  ```\n- `pkg/storage/secret/metadata/secure_value_store.go` (lines 74-75): Error status and recording combined\n\n### Advanced Patterns\n\n**Grafana Database Instrumentation:**\n- `pkg/storage/unified/sql/db/otel/otel.go`: Custom `otelDB` wrapper with `startSpan()` helper that:\n  - Consumes existing attributes from context\n  - Sets DB-specific attributes (driver name, server version)\n  - Uses `setSpanOutcome()` to record success/failure\n\n**Span Context Inspection:**\n- `rules/group.go` (lines 527-529): Checking if span is sampled and has trace ID before adding to logger\n  ```go\n  if sp.SpanContext().IsSampled() && sp.SpanContext().HasTraceID() {\n      logger = logger.With(\"trace_id\", sp.SpanContext().TraceID())\n  }\n  ```\n\n**Attributes Set During Span Creation:**\n- Prometheus and Grafana both support `trace.WithAttributes()` option during `Start()`\n- Grafana example in `pkg/services/team/teamimpl/team.go` (lines 42-43):\n  ```go\n  s.tracer.Start(ctx, \"team.CreateTeam\", trace.WithAttributes(\n      attribute.Int64(\"orgID\", cmd.OrgID),\n  ))\n  ```\n\n### File Resources for Reference\n\n- Prometheus instrumentation guide: `tracing/tracing.go`, `storage/remote/queue_manager.go`\n- Grafana instrumentation guide: `contribute/backend/instrumentation.md`\n- Prometheus span creation: `scrape/scrape.go` (scraping), `rules/group.go` (rule evaluation), `promql/engine.go` (query execution)\n- Grafana span creation: `pkg/api/*.go` (HTTP handlers), `pkg/expr/*.go` (expression execution), `pkg/tsdb/*.go` (datasource queries), `pkg/storage/**/*.go` (storage operations)\n"
